   "info" : "<table width=\"100%\" summary=\"page for lynx\"><tr><td>lynx</td><td style=\"text-align: right;\">R Documentation</td></tr></table>\\n<h2>Annual Canadian Lynx trappings 1821&ndash;1934</h2>\\n<h3>Description</h3>\\n<p>Annual numbers of lynx trappings for 1821&ndash;1934 in Canada. Taken from\\nBrockwell &amp; Davis (1991), this appears to be the series considered\\nby Campbell &amp; Walker (1977).\\n</p>\\n<h3>Usage</h3>\\n<pre>lynx</pre>\\n<h3>Source</h3>\\n<p>Brockwell, P. J. and Davis, R. A. (1991) <em>Time\\nSeries and Forecasting Methods.</em>  Second edition.\\nSpringer. Series G (page 557).\\n</p>\\n<h3>References</h3>\\n<p>Becker, R. A., Chambers, J. M. and Wilks, A. R. (1988)\\n<em>The New S Language</em>.\\nWadsworth &amp; Brooks/Cole.\\n</p>\\n<p>Campbell, M. J.and A. M.  Walker (1977).  A Survey of\\nstatistical work on the Mackenzie River series of annual\\nCanadian lynx trappings for the years  1821&ndash;1934 and\\na new analysis.\\n<em>Journal of the Royal Statistical Society series A</em>,\\n<b>140</b>, 411&ndash;431.\\n</p>\\n",
